    {
      "id": "mUIUdbagqyAn7d4pDFIfD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4600.415310580699,
      "y": 4213.119087435567,
      "width": 479.0196533203125,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "r_gegFA5k_EUDUDDBdyEn",
        "DA0XxSzLJEpZKsEVpz-H-"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2r",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1043032527,
      "version": 233,
      "versionNonce": 354330881,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "8jO3W2Eg-hh5mSRqIqYPx",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1775123787620,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What happens in zk?\n\nInstead of revealing all of w, the prover shows:\n• “I know a witness w”\n• such that all constraints are satisfied\n• while maybe only revealing the public part, like y\n\nSo here the prover could prove:\n\nI know some x such that y = x^2 + 3\n\nwithout revealing x.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What happens in zk?\n\nInstead of revealing all of w, the prover shows:\n• “I know a witness w”\n• such that all constraints are satisfied\n• while maybe only revealing the public part, like y\n\nSo here the prover could prove:\n\nI know some x such that y = x^2 + 3\n\nwithout revealing x.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
